// ██╔████╔██║███████║██║  ██║█████╗     ██║ █╗ ██║██║   ██║   ███████║   ██╔████╔██║███████║███████╗██║   ██║██╔██╗ ██║
// ██║╚██╔╝██║██╔══██║██║  ██║██╔══╝     ██║███╗██║██║   ██║   ██╔══██║   ██║╚██╔╝██║██╔══██║╚════██║██║   ██║██║╚██╗██║
// ██║ ╚═╝ ██║██║  ██║██████╔╝███████╗   ╚███╔███╔╝██║   ██║   ██║  ██║   ██║ ╚═╝ ██║██║  ██║███████║╚██████╔╝██║ ╚████║
// ╚═╝     ╚═╝╚═╝  ╚═╝╚═════╝ ╚══════╝    ╚══╝╚══╝ ╚═╝   ╚═╝   ╚═╝  ╚═╝   ╚═╝     ╚═╝╚═╝  ╚═╝╚══════╝ ╚═════╝ ╚═╝  ╚═══╝

pragma solidity ^0.8.18;

import "./mason/utils/Administrable.sol";
import "./mason/utils/Ownable.sol";
import "erc721a/contracts/extensions/ERC721ABurnable.sol";
import "erc721a/contracts/extensions/ERC721AQueryable.sol";
import "operator-filter-registry/src/DefaultOperatorFilterer.sol";
import {Base64} from "./Base64.sol";
import {Utils} from "./Utils.sol";

error ExceedsDailyLimit();
error ExceedsMaxPerWallet();
error ExceedsMaxSupply();
error InsufficientPayment();
error MismatchedArraySizes();
error TokenDoesNotExist();

contract FloorUsernameToken is
    DefaultOperatorFilterer,
    Ownable,
    Administrable,
    ERC721ABurnable,
    ERC721AQueryable
{
    struct MintConfig {
        uint64 salePrice;
        uint32 maxPerWallet;
        uint32 maxMintSupply;
        uint32 dailyLimit;
    }

    MintConfig public config;

    struct MintStats {
        uint32 tokensMintedToday;
        uint32 tokensMinted;
    }

    MintStats public stats;

    uint256 private _lastResetTimestamp = block.timestamp;

    constructor(
        string memory _tokenName,
        string memory _tokenSymbol,
        string memory _uri,
        MintConfig memory _mintConfig
    ) ERC721A(_tokenName, _tokenSymbol) {
        config = _mintConfig;
        stats = MintStats(0, 0);

        baseURI = _uri;
        treasuryAddress = msg.sender;
    }

    // ------ AIRDROPS ----------------------------------------------------------

    function airdrop(
        address _recipient,
        uint64 _quantity
    ) external onlyOperatorsAndOwner {
        _setAux(_recipient, _getAux(_recipient) + _quantity);

        _mint(_recipient, _quantity);
    }

    function airdropBatch(
        address[] calldata _recipients,
        uint64[] calldata _quantities
    ) external onlyOperatorsAndOwner {
        if (_recipients.length != _quantities.length)
            revert MismatchedArraySizes();

        for (uint256 i; i < _recipients.length; ) {
            _setAux(_recipients[i], _getAux(_recipients[i]) + _quantities[i]);

            _mint(_recipients[i], _quantities[i]);

            unchecked {
                ++i;
            }
        }
    }

    // ------- MINTING ----------------------------------------------------------

    function mint(
        uint64 _quantity
    )
        external
        payable
        requireActiveSale
        enforceMaxPerWallet(_quantity)
        enforceMaxSupply(_quantity)
        requirePayment(_quantity)
    {
        _mintTokens(_quantity);
    }

    function _mintTokens(uint64 _quantity) private {
        _resetDailyLimit();

        if (stats.tokensMintedToday + _quantity > config.dailyLimit)
            revert ExceedsDailyLimit();

        stats.tokensMinted += uint32(_quantity);
        stats.tokensMintedToday += uint32(_quantity);
        _mint(msg.sender, _quantity);
    }

    function _resetDailyLimit() private {
        if (block.timestamp >= _lastResetTimestamp + 1 days) {
            stats.tokensMintedToday = 0;
            _lastResetTimestamp = block.timestamp;
        }
    }

    // ------- BURNING ----------------------------------------------------------

    error InsufficientTokens();

    function burnForUsername(
        address _owner,
        uint256 _count
    ) external payable onlyOperatorsAndOwner {
        if (balanceOf(_owner) < _count) revert InsufficientTokens();

        uint256[] memory tokensOwned = this.tokensOfOwner(_owner);
        for (uint256 i; i < _count; ) {
            _burn(tokensOwned[i]);

            unchecked {
                ++i;
            }
        }
    }

    function burnTokens(
        uint256[] calldata tokenIds
    ) external payable onlyOperatorsAndOwner {
        for (uint256 i; i < tokenIds.length; ) {
            if (!_exists(tokenIds[i])) revert TokenDoesNotExist();
            _burn(tokenIds[i]);

            unchecked {
                ++i;
            }
        }
    }

    // ------- FINANCIAL --------------------------------------------------------

    address public treasuryAddress;

    function setTreasuryAddress(
        address _treasuryAddress
    ) external onlyOperatorsAndOwner {
        treasuryAddress = _treasuryAddress;
    }

    function release() external onlyOperatorsAndOwner {
        payable(treasuryAddress).transfer(address(this).balance);
    }

    // ------- ADMIN ------------------------------------------------------------

    function setMintConfig(
        MintConfig calldata _config
    ) external onlyOperatorsAndOwner {
        config = _config;
    }

    // ------- SELF DESTRUCT ----------------------------------------------------

    // As the Username Tokens are intended to have a finite lifespan, this method
    // is provided to allow the owner to destroy the contract and any remaining
    // tokens.
    function destruct() external onlyOperatorsAndOwner {
        selfdestruct(payable(owner()));
    }

    // ------ TOKEN METADATA ----------------------------------------------------

    string private baseURI;

    function _baseURI() internal view virtual override returns (string memory) {
        return baseURI;
    }

    function baseTokenURI() external view returns (string memory) {
        return baseURI;
    }

    function setBaseURI(string calldata _uri) external onlyOperatorsAndOwner {
        baseURI = _uri;
    }

    function _startTokenId() internal view virtual override returns (uint256) {
        return 1;
    }

    // ------ BOILERPLATE -------------------------------------------------------

    function supportsInterface(
        bytes4 interfaceId
    )
        public
        view
        override(IERC721A, ERC721A, AccessControlEnumerable)
        returns (bool)
    {
        return ERC721A.supportsInterface(interfaceId);
    }

    function setApprovalForAll(
        address operator,
        bool approved
    ) public override(ERC721A, IERC721A) onlyAllowedOperatorApproval(operator) {
        super.setApprovalForAll(operator, approved);
    }

    function approve(
        address operator,
        uint256 tokenId
    )
        public
        payable
        override(ERC721A, IERC721A)
        onlyAllowedOperatorApproval(operator)
    {
        super.approve(operator, tokenId);
    }

    function transferFrom(
        address from,
        address to,
        uint256 tokenId
    ) public payable override(ERC721A, IERC721A) onlyAllowedOperator(from) {
        super.transferFrom(from, to, tokenId);
    }

    function safeTransferFrom(
        address from,
        address to,
        uint256 tokenId
    ) public payable override(ERC721A, IERC721A) onlyAllowedOperator(from) {
        super.safeTransferFrom(from, to, tokenId);
    }

    function safeTransferFrom(
        address from,
        address to,
        uint256 tokenId,
        bytes memory data
    ) public payable override(ERC721A, IERC721A) onlyAllowedOperator(from) {
        super.safeTransferFrom(from, to, tokenId, data);
    }

    // ------ MODIFIERS ---------------------------------------------------------

    modifier enforceMaxPerWallet(uint64 quantity) {
        if (
            balanceOf(msg.sender) - _getAux(msg.sender) + quantity >
            config.maxPerWallet
        ) revert ExceedsMaxPerWallet();
        _;
    }

    modifier requirePayment(uint64 quantity) {
        if (msg.value < config.salePrice * quantity)
            revert InsufficientPayment();
        _;
    }

    modifier enforceMaxSupply(uint64 quantity) {
        if (stats.tokensMinted + uint32(quantity) > config.maxMintSupply)
            revert ExceedsMaxSupply();
        _;
    }
}
"
